!</h2><div class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Yes exactly! Here's the simple order:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>First, create the folder:</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Go to your Desktop (or wherever you want to save it)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Right click → <strong>New Folder</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Name it <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">part-4-ai-solution-design</code></li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Then open it in VS Code:</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Open VS Code</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>File</strong> → <strong>Open Folder</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Select the folder you just created</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click <strong>Select Folder</strong></li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Then open the terminal inside VS Code:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Press <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">Ctrl + backtick (</code>)` — that's the key just below Escape</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">You should now see a terminal at the bottom of VS Code. Tell me when you see it and I'll give you the next commands to run!</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Also, I love the topic change — <strong>"How Agentic AI will help Finance in the future"</strong> is a much more interesting and unique angle. Things like AI agents doing automated portfolio management, fraud detection autonomously, loan approvals without human intervention etc. Much better than plain fraud detection. 👍</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
